@startuml codex-mid-turn-steering-flow

title Codex mid-turn steering — sendMessage active-turn route

actor User
participant "SessionDetail\nComposerSdk" as UI
participant "preload API" as Preload
participant "main IPC\nadapter:send-message" as IPC
participant "AdapterRegistry\n+ Codex adapter" as Adapter
participant "CodexSdkBridge" as Bridge
participant "InternalSession" as Session
participant "CodexAppServerThread" as Thread
participant "Codex app-server\n--stdio" as Server
participant "eventBus / store" as Events

== Active turn establishes steer target ==

Bridge -> Thread: runStreamed(input)
Thread -> Server: thread/start|resume if needed
Thread -> Server: turn/start { threadId, input }
Server --> Thread: response { turn.id }
Server --> Bridge: notification turn/started { turn.id }
Bridge -> Session: currentTurnId = turn.id
Bridge -> Events: translate streaming notifications
Events --> UI: session.activity = working

== User sends from unified composer ==

User -> UI: type correction while turn is working
UI -> Preload: sendAdapterMessage(agentId, sessionId, { text })
Preload -> IPC: invoke adapter:send-message
IPC -> Adapter: sendMessage(sessionId, text, attachments?)
Adapter -> Bridge: sendMessage(sessionId, text, attachments?)
Bridge -> Session: read currentTurn + currentTurnId + pendingMessages

alt no active turn id OR message has attachments
  Bridge -> Session: pendingMessages.push(input)
  opt turn loop not running
    Bridge -> Thread: runTurnLoop(next pending input)
  end
  Bridge -> Events: emit user message { role:user }
  Events --> UI: show queued/normal user message
else active text-only turn
  Bridge -> Thread: steer(text, expectedTurnId=currentTurnId)
  Thread -> Server: turn/steer { threadId, expectedTurnId, input }
  alt review / compact / id mismatch / completed
    Server --> Thread: JSON-RPC error
    Thread --> UI: error surfaced through sendMessage
  else accepted
    Server --> Thread: result { turnId }
    Bridge -> Events: emit user message { role:user, steer:true }
    Events --> UI: show correction in transcript
  end
end

== Turn continues ==

Server --> Bridge: item/* deltas + completions
Bridge -> Events: app-server translate + token usage
Server --> Bridge: turn/completed { turn.id, status }
Bridge -> Session: currentTurnId = null
Bridge -> Events: finished

note right of Server
  turn/steer does not emit turn/started.
  It accepts input only; no model/cwd/sandbox override.
end note

note right of Bridge
  Explicit steerTurn(sessionId,text) remains a low-level adapter API.
  UI / teammate / CLI send paths converge on sendMessage;
  Codex sendMessage decides steer vs pending queue from live state.
end note

@enduml
